## üß© Overview

This project demonstrates how to deploy a **Public Key Infrastructure (PKI)** using **Active Directory Certificate Services (AD CS)** on a **Microsoft Azure-hosted Windows Server 2022 Datacenter**.  
It establishes a trusted **Enterprise Root Certificate Authority (CA)** for the internal domain `EdenSound.local`, enabling secure certificate-based authentication and encryption across the network.

---

## ‚òÅÔ∏è Environment Setup

| Component | Details |
|------------|----------|
| **VM Name** | ADServer1 |
| **Cloud Platform** | Microsoft Azure |
| **Operating System** | Windows Server 2022 Datacenter (Azure Edition) |
| **vCPUs / RAM** | 2 vCPUs / 8 GB RAM |
| **Public IP** | 172.179.128.86 |
| **Private IP** | 172.16.0.4 |
| **Domain** | EdenSound.local |
| **Connection Method** | Native RDP (Port 3389 open) |

üì∏ **Azure Virtual Machine Overview**

![Azure VM Overview](assets/Screenshot_2025-11-12_3.55.34PM.png)
![Azure RDP Connection](assets/Screenshot_2025-11-12_3.55.19PM.png)

---

## üéØ Project Objective

To configure and deploy an **Enterprise Root Certificate Authority (CA)** using AD CS integrated with **Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS)** for secure identity validation and certificate lifecycle automation.

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è Implementation Steps

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Azure & Domain Setup
- Created **ADServer1** VM in Azure.  
- Installed **Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS)**.  
- Promoted the server to a **Domain Controller** for `EdenSound.local`.  
- Configured **DNS zones** and verified forward lookups.

üì∏ *Active Directory & DNS Verification*  
![AD DS Setup](assets/Screenshot_2025-11-12_1.04.27PM.jpeg)
![DNS Zones](assets/Screenshot_2025-11-12_11.08.49AM.jpeg)

---

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ AD CS Installation
- Installed **Active Directory Certificate Services** via Server Manager.  
- Chose **Enterprise Root CA** as setup type.  
- Cryptographic Provider: RSA#Microsoft Software Key Storage Provider  
- Hash Algorithm: SHA256  
- Key Length: 2048 bits  
- Validity: 10 years (expires 11/12/2035)

üì∏ *AD CS Configuration Wizard*  
![Setup Type](assets/Screenshot_2025-11-12_11.27.00AM.png)
![Confirmation](assets/Screenshot_2025-11-12_11.28.38AM.png)
![Configuration Succeeded](assets/Screenshot_2025-11-12_11.32.53AM.png)

---

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Certification Authority Verification
- Opened `certsrv.msc` to verify **EdenSound-RootCA** was active.  
- Checked permissions under *Security tab* for **Authenticated Users**, **Domain Admins**, and **Enterprise Admins**.  
- Verified **CA certificate** presence in the Trusted Root store.

üì∏ *Certification Authority & Root Store*  
![Certification Authority Console](assets/Screenshot_2025-11-12_11.34.13AM.png)
![Root Certificates](assets/Screenshot_2025-11-12_12.52.46PM.jpeg)

